    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About Detox Gummies</h2>

    <details class="fq"><summary>Do detox gummies actually work?</summary><p>Specific ingredients can support your body's natural detoxification systems. Milk thistle protects liver cells, ACV supports digestion, and fiber aids waste elimination. No supplement "detoxifies" independently — they support existing organ function.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>What ingredients should I look for?</summary><p>Milk thistle (silymarin) for liver protection, apple cider vinegar for digestion, dandelion root for bile production, turmeric for anti-inflammatory support, and fiber for elimination. Avoid products with harsh laxatives like senna.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>How long should you take detox gummies?</summary><p>Most protocols recommend 2-4 weeks with a break. Milk thistle can be used up to 12 weeks. ACV can be taken daily. Avoid continuous use of products with laxative herbs for more than 7-10 days.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Are detox gummies safe?</summary><p>Products with well-studied ingredients (milk thistle, ACV, turmeric, fiber) are generally safe. Avoid laxative-containing products long-term. Milk thistle may interact with liver-metabolized medications. Consult your healthcare provider.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Can detox gummies help with weight loss?</summary><p>Detox gummies are not weight loss supplements. Initial weight changes are typically water weight. ACV has modest evidence for appetite suppression and insulin sensitivity. For sustainable weight loss, view these as digestive support, not fat loss tools.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>What is the difference between detox and liver support gummies?</summary><p>Liver support gummies focus on hepatoprotective ingredients (milk thistle, NAC, artichoke). Detox gummies are broader, combining liver support with digestive aids and anti-inflammatory compounds. For liver health specifically, a dedicated liver formula is more effective.</p></details>

